<subSubSection id="7930827EC283AD4A91CB0B0D45940FF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="C906478D847D4E518A0119A9F7B17D7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
8d. 
<taxonomicName id="64B44001583999BC0F28634FC4851875" LSID="57EB0B02-1E34-56D5-B754-9E028A7C739F" authority="(Boiss. &amp; C. I. Blanche) Eggens, F. Jafari &amp; Oxelman, comb. et" authorityName="Eggens &amp; Jafari &amp; Thollesson &amp; Crameri &amp; Zarre &amp; Oxelman" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Boiss. &amp; C. I. Blanche" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene microsperma subsp. modesta" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="microsperma" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="modesta">Silene microsperma subsp. modesta (Boiss. &amp; C.I.Blanche) Eggens, F.Jafari &amp; Oxelman, comb. et</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="49B9F13091BACA309CEF3A4E94FE06A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="12CDAF6EEFA85D2576AAA22B8AB05221" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="1BEE19E00D65C5EFE93B478AFA141E6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5FD9D3BCF86A6FB046455D9F51BA443" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
20.0-50.0 cm tall, erect or sometimes spreading. Stem scabrous, pubescent in lower part, scabrous, glabrous with sessile glands in upper part; with 4-10 distinct internodes, the uppermost internode 3.0-6.0 cm long and obviously longer than the next upper internode. Cauline leaves oblanceolate 10.0-40.0 
<normalizedToken id="61507C3661FE96AC93C0394C66B1FDD0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.0-4.0 mm, pubescent. Calyx 13.0-15.0 mm long, campanulate at anthesis and clavate in fruit, pubescent, scabrous; teeth unequal; shorter ones 2.0-3.0 mm, ovate, acuminate; longer ones 2.0-4.0 mm, lanceolate, acuminate; marginal hairs long (longer than 0.5 mm), dense. Inflorescence non-divaricate, branch axile (much) less than 90°. Petal claws 8.0-9.0 mm long, ciliate; limbs 3.0 mm long, bifid, white to pink, lobes oblong, petal limbs cleft to middle or more; coronal scales ca 1.0 mm long, ovate, apex entire or slightly erose. Anthophore 2.5-3.5 mm long, densely puberulent. Anthers included; filaments 6.0-9.0 mm long, glabrous or sparsely pubescent. Styles included. First pedicel 1.0-3.0 cm in flower, 2.0-4.0 cm in fruit, erect, glabrous, apex antrorse. Capsule 9.0-11.0 mm long, oblong or ellipsoid, robust. Seeds 0.6-0.8 mm wide, 0.6-0.7 mm high, testa smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1EDBCA8837C2EE94F25A05CD61AF6E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D529B6673CEB0D5B9055E01607BD463A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4150F3887868A9FB8143293F4AE0220" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Palestine, Lebanon (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="93420EA67D5F915241CE1C790AF427ED" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of S. sect. Arenosae. Each color code corresponds to one taxon: A S. arenosa B S. austroiranica C S. chaetodonta D S. exsudans E S. georgievskyi F S. leyseroides G S. linearis H S. microsperma subsp. cypria I S. microsperma subsp. maritima J S. microsperma subsp. microsperma K S. microsperma subsp. modesta L S. striata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447291" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="301C91AEABC8668FEABF21CA7D458411" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9A301C61931B225165307D3DB2DB1B58" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7659BE69F824B706C4D19F22247E4048" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Distinguished by the short anthophore and long capsule that is unusually thick-walled and robust. This taxon has all the characteristics of a self-pollinating 
<taxonomicName id="07DC954E0951C0786D925FAFA829477B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8D5E31A8AFF37CA0BCF5E3B0BBD5128D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. short anthophore, large capsule, small petal limbs, and anthers and styles included in the corolla mouth (
<bibRefCitation id="5E42C78AB97F5879CA9EC69686DE81EB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0106990" author="Aydin, Z" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B3" refString="Aydin, Z, Marcussen, T, Ertekin, AS, Oxelman, B, 2014b. Marginal likelihood estimate comparisons to obtain optimal species delimitations in Silenesect.Cryptoneurae (Caryophyllaceae). PLoS One 9(9): e106990. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0106990" title="Marginal likelihood estimate comparisons to obtain optimal species delimitations in Silenesect. Cryptoneurae (Caryophyllaceae). PLoS One 9 (9): e 106990." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0106990" year="2014 b">Aydin et al. 2014b</bibRefCitation>
). This taxon used to be considered as closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="964E88B9735A8B42BF9017E5244DD394" genus="S." lsidName="S. chaetodonta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chaetodonta">
<emphasis id="82FD999A1D11A1D9C7E9026A263B926E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. chaetodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the molecular phylogenies (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B40B5F43E388B2924C64F29ACE8CDA02" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Species tree from two STACEY runs and three unlinked regions (ITS, RPB 2, rps 16). Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.75 are shown above branches. The number following the taxonomic name is the specimen ID (Suppl. material 1). Scale bar reﬂects the number of substitutions per site." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447285" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="692AE7EC64164C9188F944583D976D41" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Phylogenetic tree resulting from Bayesian analysis of the ITS sequences including 76 taxa. The trees were summarized in a 50 % majority-rule consensus tree with the posterior probabilities (PP) indicated above branches. Bootstrap support values (&gt; 75 %) based on MP and ML are noted below branches, respectively. The numbers following the taxonomic name indicate the specimen ID and Genbank numbers (Suppl. material 1), respectively." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447287" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="23E9F3F622299554685C83F5E6990C78" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Phylogenetic tree resulting from Bayesian analysis of the RPB 2 sequences including 76 taxa. The trees were summarized in a 50 % majority-rule consensus tree with the posterior probabilities (PP) indicated above branches. Bootstrap support values (&gt; 75 %) based on MP and ML are noted below branches, respectively. The numbers following the taxonomic name indicate the specimen ID and Genbank numbers (Suppl. material 1), respectively." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.159.51500.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/447289" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
) show that &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="1187F93DEC4CC075F6BF063EB055C4FC" genus="S." lsidName="S. modesta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="5771046DD3681AA8E640B367C5A31B65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="CE519167849569BFC1E0696E188E126A" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="89CE494BAA1CB4963FA7B19C8BBA6D7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. In order to emphasize this information, we have therefore decided to treat this taxon as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C0FD5748B101CAB86431F164C8DDB3CF" genus="S." lsidName="S. microsperma" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="A61E5BA5E69D5968E9A96EF9B8C49E48" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than recognizing it as a species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
